-- U.S., South Africa Sign Partnership Framework Agreement on Fighting AIDS
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-12-15T05:29:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/u-s-south-africa-sign-partnership-framework-agreement-on-fighting-aids.html
The U.S. and South Africa signed a
partnership agreement that will guide efforts on fighting
HIV/AIDS in the African nation, the U.S. Embassy based in
Pretoria said in an e-mailed statement today.  The agreement was signed in Washington yesterday by U.S.
Secretary of State Hillary Clinton and South African
International Relations and Cooperation Minister Maite Nkoana-
Mashabane.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  